inn1.comm: on target: It landed on a good length, around middle and off, moved towards the off stump, tapped to the off side
well down the leg side and Ramdin can't reach. Blewett, on air, says the 'keeper could have done better than that.
on the leg and middle, full and turned to midwicket region for a single
rushes through the off stump channel, Watson has a poke before withdrawing his bat
shifts his weight to the back foot and steers a back-of-length delivery to third man
the first bouncer of the day and Marsh goes down under
short in length, around the off stump, dabbed to third man for a single
good probing delivery, slanting across Marsh who lets it go through to Ramdin
similar delivery and again left alone.
lands outside off, on a length and moves further away, left alone
back of length, cutting away from Marsh who mistimes a cut to point. Does some gardening down the track now.
slashed to third man boundary. Width outside off and Marsh didn't quite go towards the line but went hard at the flash

edged past the second slip. Fuller and around the off stump, Marsh pushes hard at it, bat well away from the body and watched it sail past the slip fielder. It would have gone straight to the third slip's hands.
slings it full outside leg and Watson tickles it to the fine-leg region whwere Nikita Miller fumbles as he dives to his right
lands full on the middle and swung away a touch, Watson is squared up as he is looking to dab across the line, adjusts to push it down the track
a sharp bouncer on the left shoulder, Watson shapes to pull but doesn't connect well. The ball rolls towards midwicket. Fidel stares at Watson who has some thing to say back at Fidel
short in length, leans forward to defend
on the middle and leg, clipped off the pads to deep square leg boundary.
outside the off stump and Ramdin gathers
fuller, around the off stump, driven to mid-off
length delivery around the off stump, steered to point
run down to third man
rushing outside the off stump, left alone
quite similar to the last ball of the previous over. On the legs and Watto flicks it away to the deep square leg boundary.
on a length, around middle and leg, tries to turn it to the leg side and it runs off the pad to the off side
fuller, outside off stump and squeezed past covers
length delivery around the off and middle, defended to the off side
outside the off stump, full in length, Watson gets forward, opens the bat-face and runs it to third man
Marsh ducks into a bouncer.
fuller, on the middle and off and Marsh jabs it to point
full delivery coming in a touch and Watson defends and it runs off the inner edge to the on side
kicks up from short of length, on the middle stump line, defended to the off side, thinks about a run and changes minds as Powell rushes across
angled across Marsh who shoulders arms
just outside the off stump, on a length, steered to point
just outside the off stump, on a length, defended to covers
slanted across Marsh who lets it go through to Ramdin
full and well outside the off stump, swing and a miss
not all that short but Watson goes for the pull and is beaten
short in length and drifting towards middle and leg, Watson goes back and punches it through midwicket.  Mere push and it fairly raced off the turf. Very fast outfield.
gets forward to place a length delivery to right of mid-on for a single
leans forward to defend to the on side
leans forward to turn a full delivery to midwicket
Banged in short and Watson goes for the pull and top edges it over Ramdin's head. Good pace and carry.
fuller and driven to mid-on.
another one dug in short but it tails down leg side
full pitched and Watson mistimes a drive to covers. He then remarks his guard with his spikes.
First the bouncer, then the really full one and now the length delivery cutting in from outside off. Watson shapes to drive on the up and it runs off the inner edge to left of Ramdin
gets on top of the bounce of a back-of-length delivery angling away from him and pushes it to covers
a tad wide outside off and a touch short in length and Marsh goes for the cut, again reaching well away from him and gets a bottom edge to the off side
length delivery on the off and middle, played with soft hands to the off side and they cross over for a single

sharp, well-directed bouncer on the middle stump line and Hussey hops, takes hie eyes off but manages to drop the ball in front of him. The bottom-hand was taken of the handle and he got on top of the bounce
slings a full one around the off stump and Hussey leans forward to defend to covers
pushed across Hussey who lets it angle past him
short in length, outside the off stump, mistimes the cut shot to covers.
strays on to the legs, flicked to deep midwicket
leans forward to defend to covers
drifts to the legs again, placed to left of mid-on for a single
again on the legs, off the length this time and tucked behind square leg
shifts his line to outside off but Marsh is quick to lean across and creams it through covers
outside the off stump, steered to backward point
shout for lbw but the ball pitched outside leg stump before moving in to strike Hussey in front of the stumps.
outside the off stump, moving away, left alone
back of length, on the leg and middle line, clipped past square leg
again on the pads, turned straight to square leg this time.
just outside the off stump, cut down to third man
short in length, outside the off stump, moving away and Hussey cuts to left of third man. Not much power behind that; he just concentrated on getting the placement right
leans across to drive a full pitched delivery to sweeper cover
short in length, on the middle and off, Marsh stays adjacent to the line, opens the bat-face and guides to backward point
Powell and Ramdin combo are at it again. It landed on the leg stump line, on a length and Marsh tried to play it through the on side but the ball cut across him and clipped the outer edge
leans across, covers the off stump and lets a length delivery whiz past the off stump
moves outside the off stump, left alone
fullish, on the middle and off, squeezed of the outer edge to backward point
gets forward and across and leaves a delivery moving outside the off stump
on the off stump and Hussey gets close to the line to defend to the off side
similar delivery and Hussey pushes it to covers
off cutter, moving from middle and off towards off, nudged to the off side
fuller and Hussey leans forward to drive to left of deep cover for couple of runs
cuts in from outside off stump, Clarke stands tall to punch it back down the track and Powell lunges to his right to make the stop
fuller, shapes in from outside off and Clarke gets on to the front foot to nudge it to midwicket
The debutante Miller makes a fab diving stop to his left at mid-off. It was crashed by Clarke and Miller made a fine half-stop
the yorker on the middle and off, jabbed to left of mid-off for a quick single. There is a direct hit but Hussey is home
banged in short, climbs chest-high around the off stump and run down to third man
short in length, moving outside the off stump, worked to backward point
full, straight, outside off, Clarke has a flash and can't connect. Hussey has a word with him.
back of the length, outside off stump and Clarke punches it on the up and to left of short cover where Gayle makes a diving half stop
shout for lbw as the ball nips back to evade the waft and strikes him high on the pad
Ah the first free hit of the game coming up as Bravo oversteps
low full toss, on the leg side, Clarke opens his stance, has a swing, misses and it runs off the pads to the off side
slanted across him, cut down to third man
leans forward to drive to left of mid-off
slower one, full and on the middle, worked through wide mid-on. Clarke has reached 4000 ODI runs.
dug in short, outside off, Clarke gets his bat in a horizontal position and taps the ball to point.
short in length, outside off stump, pushed to cover point for a quick single
another slower one, dabbed to backward point
lovely off drive. He leaned into the shot and drove the full pitched delivery through wide mid-off region
cutting away from Hussey who steers to backward point
full and outside off stump, bottom edges a square slash to the off side
leans forward to wrist a full length delivery on middle through wide mid-on region. Very well timed.
shifts his line to outside off stump, punched through cover point
leans forward to drive to right of mid-off and even though, Findlay fires in a direct hit at the striker's end, Clarke is home in time.
length delivery shaping in towards middle stump, pushed to mid-on
drifts to the legs, flicked through midwicket region. Findlay slips while picking the ball and falls to the ground. By the time he recovers, they turn for the third run
gets forward to a length delivery and punches to left of mid-off
leans across to push to cover point for a single
fullish, on the middle and leg stump line, whipped to midwicket boundary. Good use of the wrists.
leans forward to defend to covers
slower one, shaping in to the off stump, worked to midwicket
leans forward to defend to mid-on
full and outside off stump, mistimes a square slash to point
further outside off, full, driven to covers
steered through backward point
full and on the middle and leg, turned past square leg
short and Hussey rocks back to pull to wide midwicket boundary
fuller and driven past the lunging short extra cover to mid-off
full pitched delivery around the off stump, driven to covers
a tad slower, a touch short in length, Hussey bends his back knee and taps the ball towards gully
full and outside off, driven to left of mid-off
leans forward to work a full one through midwicket
full pitched outside off, driven to covers
Easy. Short and slipping down leg, pulled to fine-leg boundary
corrects his line, gets it towards off and middle, defended down the track
on the off stump line, pushed back to the bowler
fuller and on the middle, shaping in, flicked to midwicket
on the middle and leg, worked to deep midwicket
outside off stump, steers to cover point region. Quick single and had the throw found the stumps, Clarke would have been run out.
short in length, outside the off stump, mistimes a cut to Sarwan at covers
just outside off stump, not much room but Hussey manages to open the bat-face and dab it to third man
bouncer and ducks under
almost scoops to short midwicket. It was a touch slower, off the scrambled seam, and Clarke was early into the forward push and it went in the air but fell short of Sarwan
leans forward to drive through the off side field
keeps a touch low after landing on length outside off, driven to long-on
leans forward to dab to midwicket
on the off and middle, not much turn, reverse swept to short third man region
floated on the off stump line, driven to long-off
stays back to punch a short-in-length delivery to long-off
on the off and middle, defended to the off side
short in length, coming into middle, turned to midwicket
sliding on to the pads and the ball rolls towards midwicket
banged in short and pulled to deep square leg fielder
comes down the track and drags a full delivery from outside off through wide mid-on region. Ugly but effective.
the slog doesn't work this time. He cleared the front foot and swung a full delivery straight to deep midwicket.
full and drifting in towards middle and off, Symonds pushes rather tentatively at that and edges to short third man
leans forward to drive to long-on
short in length, well outside off, Symonds goes back and across to carve it to deep cover
leans forward to push a floater through cover point for a single
beaten outside off stump. So far he has not got many to turn but this one did and spun past the outside edge
full and straight, driven to long-off
well outside the off stump, Symonds lets it go
full and outside off, driven towards long-on but Chris Gayle gets across quickly to cut the single
on the back foot, punches to the on side of  the track and Gayle makes the stop
goes back to push to extra cover
leans forward to defend
goes back to a quicker flatter delivery to defend
leans forward to drive to long-off
leans forward to defend
floated on the off stump, pushed back to the bowler
goes back to push to extra cover
beaten. Again that rare turn and Symonds pushes inside the line
outside off stump, no poke this time from Symonds
shout for lbw  but Bucknor turns it down. Clarke misses the sweep and was struck in front of off stump. It would have hit the middle.
goes back to push to the off side
short and outside off, going on straight, cut to deep point
Symonds has begun his show. He stretches forward to time a off drive sweetly and to wide long-off boundary
driven down the track
short and outside off, cut to backward point
leans forward to nudge to the on side
leans forward to drive to covers
drags it short and outside off, cut to deep point

another big shout for lbw and Asad Rauf lifts his finger after some delay. Another sweep that Clarke  didn't connect but he was struck marginally outside the off stump. In the  previous over, he survived a shout when he was hit on the off stump line and this time is unlucky to be given out.
low dipping full toss, stabbed towards Symonds and Nikita lunged to make the stop.
tucked away behind square for a single
a bit short and Hussey goes back to cut square and gets his first ODI run
Symonds forward and defends, they scamper through for one
pushed to cover and they get through for a single
driven down to long on and it's another easy run
on the stumps, Hussey deliberately clips this one through square leg
outside off stump, Symonds goes down to paddle a sweep in the air safely down towards fine leg
turned away fine once more, this time Findlay keeps it to one
a touch short, Hussey tries to cut and slams it into the turf, a bit of a let-off for Miller
fuller, but still pushed through quickly, and Hussey drives through cover
width outside off again, Symonds cuts to deep point
left alone outside off stump
fullish ball on off, Symonds squeezes a drive down to long on
driven back to the bowler
worked away through midwicket and there's easy runs there
Symonds tucks this one to fine leg
outside off and Hussey turns it easily behind square leg, just finding the gaps comfortably
driven back towards the bowler, Gayle tries to collect but collides slightly with Hussey, the ball gets past and the batsmen take a single
a bit short, Symonds can't beat short cover
left alone outside off
straighter now from Miller, Symonds defends
short and wide again, Symonds pinpoints extra cover
cut in the air but it drops short of gully
again Symonds can't find the gap through the off side, straight to extra cover
on the stumps, Hussey drives down to long on
quicker and flatter on the pads, Symonds turns it through midwicket
straight back to the bowler
driven to extra cover, can't beat the field
turned straight to midwicket
tossed up a little, on the pads and driven down to long on again
leans forward to drive to the off side
floated on the off stump, shapes to drive and it runs off the inner edge to the on side
stays back to punch to deep cover
slightly short of length, arm-ball on the off and Symonds stayed adjacent to the line and cut it superbly between backward point and short third man
on the middle, defended back to the bowler
short, slower and cut to left of deep cover
slings a full one outside off stump, left alone
outside the off stump and left alone
short in length, outside off stump, punched to backward point where Chanderpaul makes a diving stop to his left
leans forward to drive a full delivery to sweeper cover
tails in towards middle and leg, whipped to deep midwicket
fires in a bouncer and Symonds ducks
leans forward to drive to long-off
comes down the track, Miller drags back the length and Symonds stabs it off the inner edge to pad
goes back to force a short-of-length delivery to wide long-off
Superbly struck six over long-on. He leaned forward and decided to go through the line of the flighted delivery and it crash landed on the roof of the commentators box.
short in length, outside off stump and cut well through backward point
Another boundary. Aussies are going for the kill. Short in length and outside off stump, Symonds waited before cutting it to left of backward point and well to the right of the wide third man
on the legs, flicked to left of long leg where a diving stop is made
square driven to deep cover.
bouncer and Hussey goes down under. One for the over
well outside the off stump, David Hussey reaches out to slash it to sweeper cover
hits the deck short of length, climbs towards the rib cage, tickled to fine leg
comes down the track, the length is shortened and he defends
the arm-ball, just outside off, dabbed to short third man
on the off stump, turned towards the on side and Miller scampers after to it make a diving stop
just outside off, skids on, cut to backward point
Not this time, though. Symonds backed away to cut it well to the right of the backward point fielder
stretches across to sweep a full delivery from outside off to deep square leg boundary. He found the gap perfectly. 50 up. Symonds on the rampage.
on the off stump line, pushed towards sweeper cover for a single
short of length, skids on towards the off stump, Symonds chops it to third man
back of length and outside off stump, cut hard to the left of third man where Fletcher makes a good tumbling stop. Gayle applauds the effort.
kicks up from short of length as it comes in, tucked behind square leg
hurls across a bouncer and Symonds lets it go over his shoulder
Another bouncer and Symonds ducks
really full and outside off, jabbed to the off side
full and outside off, Hussey tries to carve it through point and gets a thick under edge and to left of Ramdin
a tad slower, full and outside off, run down to third man for a single
yorker on the off and middle, dug out towards mid-on and Bravo cuts across to his right and dives acrobatically but can't reach and the ball rolls to mid-on
full pitched outside off, drilled to long-off
short of length, rushing through the off stump channel, Hussey cuts and misses
low full toss on the middle, Symonds moves to the leg side and drives well to the right of sweeper cover. Lovely placement. No violence.
just short of the blockhole, on the legs, turned past square leg
slower, short in length and outside off, cut down to third man
stabs a yorker on the middle and leg back down the wicket
spears down leg and Ramdin dives to collect
slower one, full and just outside leg, shoveled to deep backward square leg
banged in short of length, coming into Symonds who arches back to play a neat short-arm pull to wide midwicket boundary.
moves outside the leg stump and crashes a full delivery on the off stump to deep cover
full and on the legs, nudged to the on side
David Hussey, who sparkled in the IPL, joins in the fun. The left leg is cleared, the bat comes across and the short-of-length delivery disappears into the grassy banks at midwicket
fuller, whipped through the on side for a single
almost yorker length on the off and middle, pushed to long-off
full pitched just outside off, driven to deep cover
short in length, outside off, dabbed to backward point
comes down the track, Miller drags back the length again and Hussey has to be contend with a single with a tap to cover point
Hammered to deep extra cover boundary. This is wonderful batting. Not too many risks but he is upping the ante at will. He rocks back to force a short-of-length delivery through the off side.
Oh the reverse sweep but played back of the bat! He didn't bother to switch to the front side and paddled a length delivery on the middle to third man boundary.
leans forward to work through midwicket
goes back to push a delivery outside off to covers
full pitched on the middle and leg, turned to deep midwicket
yorker length delivery but slips down leg
well-directed yorker on the middle, stabbed to the on side, Bravo cuts across the pitch and dives to prevent the single
yorker length again, on the off stump line, jabbed to point
clears the front foot and drags the really full delivery to square leg

the yorkers keep coming from Bravo. This one is jabbed out to the on side, Bravo rushes across and fires in a throw at the striker's end where Symonds dives to get back. But had Bravo hit the stumps, Symonds would have been run out. What a athlete  Bravo is.
comes down the track, moves outside leg and drills a full pitched delivery on the stumps to long-off
Brutal. Super clean swing of the bat and the ball has disappeared over long-on. He moved outside leg. The bat came down. Met the ball flush in the middle. The white ball soared into the orbit.
low full toss on the pads as he tried to follow Symonds who had stepped outside leg and Symonds swings it to deep backward square leg boundary.
moves outside the leg, has a big swing towards wide long-on, inside edges to short fine-leg. He then practices hitting into the V
low full toss on the leg stump, Symonds was outside leg and flashes it to long leg
Hussey follows Symonds. He steps down leg, the bowler follows him and he swings the full delivery to left of long leg where its kicked away into play
he threatens to moves towards off before going outside leg and slices a full delivery in the slot over long-off. The carnage continues.

steps down the track, clears the front foot in an effort to the get the bat swing going but Edwards fires it short of length and on the off stump. Symonds tries to flat-bat it over the off side but couldn't clear the fielder at mid-off. Super entertaining innings comes to an end.
Short delivery, Hopes tries to whip pull it  but top edges a dolly to midwicket.
full delivery, driven to long-off.
moves outside leg and drives hard and straight to covers where Gayle takes the 'catch'
yorker on the middle, he can't get under the ball and digs it out to the on side
back of length, cutting in to off and middle, pushed to cover point
another yorker on the middle, manages to dig it out to slips. Very good over this
driven past the diving bowler to long-off
floated full outside off, square driven to left of deep cover
leans forward to work a full delivery through midwicket
The low full toss does the trick.  David skipped down the track and swung a dipping delivery to the substitute fielder at deepmidwicket
short in length, on the middle, tucked to square leg
bangs it short of length and it cuts back in at Lee who had moved outside leg. Lee was cramped up, took his eyes off the ball but manages to dab it to the off side
clears his front leg and slices a full delivery on middle and off to sweeper cover.
short in length and rushing through the off stump channel, Lee is outside leg, tries to cut but misses. But a free hit coming up
digs it short, Lee is outside leg again, hops to cut but is beaten by the extra bounce and edges it to the 'keeper.

another short--pitched delivery, mistimes a pull between midwicket and deep square leg. Sarwan runs back, Findlay runs in and both stop and assume the other will take the catch and it drops right in middle of them
full delivery, jabbed away for a single
moves away and mistimes a cut to covers
a tad slower, full, driven to long-off.
full and swinging away from the off stump, Ronchi was moving outside leg, stopped his movement, crouched, reached out to slice it through backward point
full in length, swung straight to long-off. The average first-innings score on this ground is 284
steps down leg side, Bravo follows him with a low dipping full toss, scooped to front of square leg and Chanderpaul rushes from short fine leg, dives and almost gets under the ball.
yorker, stabbed to covers. Bravo has bowled very well in the end overs
finishes things off with a dot ball. He moved outside leg, Bravo fired in a low full toss outside off. Swing and a miss.

inn2.comm: full delivery, hint of swing, on the off stump, squeezed to point
Two slips in place and they watch as Xavier Marshall shoulders arms to a delivery outside off
Plumb. Lee didn't even appeal initially as he ran on straight before turning to  query Bucknor. Full, fast, tailing into middle and leg and the tentative Xavier is caught on the shuffle. Gone.
lovely straight drive to start off. He stayed beside the line of a full and straight delivery on the middle and presented the full face of the blade. Mere push and it raced away.
shifts his line to outside off and Sarwan creams the full delivery though covers. Sweetly timed.
on a length, just outside off, Sarwan stays back, hops and punches it to covers
swings down leg. Slip and short midwicket in place. It did curve back in. If he gets it to start from off and middle, it could get interesting
pushes this one across Sarwan, with the angle, left alone
full, slanting away from Sarwan who drives to covers
cuts away off the length, across Sarwan who is squared-up and pushes it to point
length delivery angling towards off, pushed down the track and Bracken fields
slanted across Sarwan who lets it go through to Ronchi
turns a full delivery to long leg
full and straight on the off and middle, driven to mid-off. Sarwan is looking to be positive here
short of length, outside off, Sarwan goes hard at the cut shot and bottom edges it to the off side.
blasted to deep point boundary. More width than the previous delivery, similar short of length and Sarwan goes back and across to cut it hard.
fuller, closer to the off stump, no swing, driven to mid-off
back of length, outside off, tapped to covers
short in length and outside off, Sarwan goes for his cut shot but mistimes it to right of Clarke at backward point
outside the off stump line, steered to backward point.
pushes a length delivery to short mid-off
fuller, coming in towards middle, tucked behind square leg
back of length, on the middle, turned to backward square leg region for a single
edged past the first slip. It held its line after landing on a length around off stump, Gayle played inside the line, tried to withdraw his bat but it ran off the outer edge past the diving Watson
The Gayle pull. Short of length, coming into him and he lifts his right leg and fists the ball through front of square
shuffles across to steer a full delivery to point
short in length, outside off stump, dabbed to third man for a single.
digs it short on middle and leg, Gayle short-arm jabs it to long leg
banged in short and it whizzes past Sarwan who withdraws the bat away from the line and lets it fly past him
well outside off stump, Sarwan can't connect with the cut shot.
stands on his toes to punch a back-of-length delivery just outside off to Symonds at covers
lets this one go through to Ronchi
full and on the leg and middle, turned straight to short midwicket
shifts his line to outside off, Gayle thinks about driving before lifting the bat above his head and Ronchi comes into play
kicks up from short of length outside off stump, Gayle cuts to deep backward point
slings a full delivery from almost round-arm action on the middle and off , defended down the track.
pushes another full delivery to extra cover
outside off, left alone
And Lee bangs a short one on the leg stump line. Up goes the front leg, down comes the bat and he laps it around the corner to fine leg
Wallop. He cleared the front foot and killed a full delivery over wide long-on.
shifts his line to outside off and is guided to backward point
full pitched outside off stump, Gayle goes hard at his drive, the bat-face shuts and the ball rolls to left of mid-off
short of length, holding its line outside off, defended down the track
leans across to push a full length delivery to Clarke at backward point who fields and runs to his left and to his right as he shouts words of encouragement to his team-mates. Nervous energy.
on the off stump line, off a length, defended down the track. Slip and short  straightish midwicket in
back of length, coming in to Gayle who nudges it toward square leg
overpitched outside off, driven to right of extra cover where Symonds makes a diving stop
short in length, outside the off stump, tapped to right of backward point
length delivery pushed across Sarwan who taps it close on the off side and rushes across for  a single
short in length, outside the off stump, pushed to the off side
full delivery on the middle, driven to Lee at mid-on
coming in towards the middle and off, defended to covers
on the middle, tailing towards middle and leg, turned to short midwicket
outside the off stump, steered to third man
full delivery on the middle, pushed to long-on
leans forward to drive to covers
on the leg and middle, kicking up back of length, dabbed to midwicket
run down to third man. 50 up.
full pitched outside off, driven to extra cover
short in length, outside off, cut to third man
down the leg side, doesn't connect with the flick shot
on a length, coming in, pushed to the on side
back of length, on the middle, tickled behind square leg
full and around the leg stump line, nudged to square leg
gets forward to push towards mid-on
fullish outside off stump, driven to long-off
full pitched outside off, mistimes a drive to covers
almost yorker length on the middle and off, driven to mid-off
similar length again, on the middle, jabbed down the track
short of length, steered to third man
leans forward to push to point
kicks up from back of length, at the body, fended behind square leg
length delivery outside off, guided to point
on the middle and leg, turned past square leg
cutting across Gayle who tries to run it through vacant slip region and is beaten. Ronchi is standing up to the stumps
low full toss, driven to long-off. I thought he was trying to drive through on side. Yep, the replays confirm that ; he got a leading edge
tailing into pads, misses to connect with his waft across the line and it rolls away to the on side off the pad
leans forward to steer a seam-up delivery outside off to short third man
on the middle, coming in, nurdled to square leg
full and outside off stump, left alone
fullish, on the off and middle, pushed to the off side
bangs in a bouncer but it's too high and Ronchi is no superman to bring it back down to earth
leans forward to push to extra cover
full pitched, driven to extra cover
on the middle and leg, nudged to the on side
breaks free with a lovely caressed straight drive. Er no. Wallops a full delivery to the straight boundary. What bat speed.
More violence. The front foot was cleared and he swung a low full toss to wide midwicket boundary.
reaches out for a full delivery outside off, the bottom-hand comes off the handle as he shapes to drive and he drags it to long-on
back of length, skids on towards middle, stabbed to the off side
outside the off stump, dabbed to third man
short in length, moves towards leg stump, clipped off the pads for couple of runs
full and angling away from Sarwan who fails to connect with a cover drive.
on the off stump line, Sarwan shuffles across, tries to work it to the on side but can only send it back to the bowler.
how does a top-order batsman like Sarwan gets squared up so often? It's a wonder. Again squared-up, to a delivery on the off and middle and gets a leading edge down the track
short of length outside off, cut to covers
short in length, coming in to Gayle who turns it past square leg
on the middle and off, this time he stays adjacent to the line and runs it down to third man
on the middle and leg, turned to square leg
short in length, cutting away from Gayle who is squared-up and adjusts to jab it to the point region
outside off, left alone.
well outside the off stump, full, Gayle reaches out to slice it to deep cover
leans forward to work a length delivery through midwicket
short of length, short-arms it towads deep midwicket. 50 for the skipper.
leans forward to push a full delivery to mid-on
short in length, outside off stump, punched to point
full and just outside the off stump, pushed to covers
outside the off stump, squeezed to wide third man
full pitched outside off, driven to left of sweeper cover
back of length, on the middle and leg, clipped to long leg
Sarwan welcomes him with a well-timed and even better, well-placed cover drive ,. well to the right of the sweeper cover
stretches across to get a single to point region
from round the stumps, full and on the middle, driven to long-off
goes back to turn a delivery turning into him to Hopes at square leg
short of length, outside off, cut to deep point
fullish, on the off stump line, driven back down the track
short in length, lapped around the corner behind square leg
dabbed to third man for yet another single
leans forward to work it to the on side
low full toss outside off stump, slashed to deep cover
slips down leg side, misses the glance and it runs off the pad to fine leg boundary
down the leg side
driven powerfully to long-on
leans forward to ease a full delivery to long-on
really full delivery outside off, jabbed to David
gets forward to tap a delivery outside off to backward point
Shot boss. He waltzed down the track, reached the pitch and lifted a flighted delivery straight over the bowler's head.
skips down to drive to long-off. 50 for Sarwan
on the pads, turned to long leg
back of length, outside off stump, skids on to Gayle who chops it to backward point
slower one, full, square drive through cover point
full length delivery outside off, guided to Lee at third man
Low full toss. The bat comes down. Blink. The ball is picked up from extra cover boundary
leans forward to defend down the track
outside the off stump, cut down to third man
back of length, coming in, punched to long-on
pushes a length delivery to the off side
short in length, sits up outside off and Sarwan flat-bats it to long-off.
short in length, forced to long-on
on the leg and middle, worked past square leg. Three Aussies converge on the ball.
Oh ho Sarwan has creamed that. He backed to the legside and slapped a short-of-length delivery just outside off stump. Talk about intent.
And now a delicate late cut. He waited for the ball to come to him, opened the bat-face and glided it through vacant slip region
The bouncer. Sarwan pulls but bottom edges it to the ground and Ronchi dives. The battle is on

Lee takes out Sarwan. It kicked up from short of length and came in from outside off, Sarwan wanted to punch it square off the back foot, the bat went outside the line and he feathered a inner edge. Enter Chanders.
short in length, outside off, dabbed to point
gets behind the line of a short-of-length delivery and turns it to the on side.
on the middle and leg, turned to deep midwicket
short of length outside off stump, nudged to the on side.
full length outside off stump, steered to backward point
kicks up from a length, Chanderpaul looks to defend, is surprised at the extra bounce, takes the bottom-hand off the handle and jabs the ball to the on side
leans forward to turn a full length delivery behind square leg
slips to the pads, turned straight to Lee at short fine leg.
short in length and outside off stump, Chanderpaul gets up and running with a cut shot.
swing and a miss. Full, outside off stump, Chanderpaul slashed hard but no wood on leather
Chanders pings the extra cover boundary. He went down on his knee to scoop a full delivery - a slower one  - outside off over the off side field
short in length and outside off, cut to backward point
fuller, driven towards mid-off for a quick single.
on the middle stump line, wristed to deep square leg region for a single
short in length, outside off stump, pushed down to long-on for a single
short in length and Chanderpaul fetches it from outside off and drags his pull to long leg
on the middle and leg, nudged to midwicket region for a quick single. The bearded Symonds with the throw but he misses and Gayle survives
leans forward to turn a full length delivery to Symonds. They don't attempt a run now
on the middle and off, turned around the corner to the right of Lee at short fine leg
The high bouncer. It sails well above Chanderpaul
fuller, on the middle and leg, tries to turn it to square leg and gets a leading edge t o third man
the yorker ends up as a low full toss, pushed down the track. Free hit coming up folks
The slow bouncer, Gayle waits before pulling it to deep midwicket boundary. Tragi comedy there. Marsh has his eyes fixed on the ball which sails over him and he trips over the boundary hoardings.
pushed to the off side
leans forward to push a full delivery back to Lee
length delivery on the off and middle, squeezed to cover point
tip and run. Pushed to mid-off and Gayle retains the strike with a quick dash across
leans forward to jab a length delivery coming in to the middle. Scrambled seam and Gayle was early into the drive and edges it to his pad
back of length, just outside off, punched back to the bowler.
on the hips, tucked to left of midwicket.
cut and a miss. Short of length delivery outside off and Chanderpaul goes for the shot
steered to the off side
punched to long-on for a single
floated outside off stump, full and Gayle murders it to long-on boundary. Wham.
driven back to the bowler
leans forward to on drive to long-on
dips in front of the middle, full, worked to midwicket
turns in, driven to midwicket
leans forward to wrist a full delivery to midwicket
turned past square leg
gets behind the line of a length delivery and works it past square leg for a single.
on the pads, turned to right of short third man and Lee fires in a throw at the non-striker's end. Gayle is in. The ball misses the stumps.
length delivery on the off stump, pushed to point
slower one, shapes in from outside off, turned to midwicket
short of length, turned to long leg
back of length, outside off, cut to backward point
outside the off stump, run down to third man
leans forward to push a length delivery to mid-off
full and on the middle, squeezed to left of point
on the middle and off, turned to midwicket
leans forward to push a full delivery through the on side
0n the middle and leg, clipped to midwicket. Clarke fields and turns around to have a  shy at the non-striker's end
short in length, on the leg stump line, clipped off the pads to deep square leg
short in length, skidding outside off, pushed to covers
Massive! Imperious. He moved the front leg out of the way and muscled a length delivery to wide long stands. West Indies now need 97 to win
fuller, outside off, dragged to long-on
on a length, outside off stump, cut down to point
on a length, moving away from Gayle who steers to backward point
and again. Three dot balls. Watson who likes to bowl short normally has kept them fuller today
Perhaps thinking Gayle will go after this ball, pushes it well wide off the off stump

Australia break through. Watto strikes. Hopes takes a very good catch. Gayle's fine innings comes to an end. He wanted to swing a full delivery to the leg side but ended up slicing it high in the air towards cover point. It came down swirling in the air, Hopes moved to his side, managed to fix his eye on the ball and hung on to it. Big blow. Enter Bravo.
turned to midwicket
fullish, just outside off stump, pushed past the bowler
Chanders takes over. He thrust his front foot out and lifted a length delivery over wide mid-on region. 90 from 94 balls.
clips this one to right of long leg.
comes in from just outside off, punched to Symonds at extra cover.
he leans across to place a ball from outside off stump through wide mid-on region
punches to long-on for a single.
leans forward to turn to midwicket
full again, outside off stump, pushed to left of mid-on where Symonds - he seems to be every where - dives to make the stop.
on the pads, turned to long leg for a single
leans forward to drive to mid-off
well outside the off stump, a tad slower and Chanderpaul fails to connect with his cut shot
glances to deep backward square leg for a single. 84 from 84 now.
short in length, just outside the off stump, Chanderpaul cuts but straight to backward point. Tense faces in the stands. 84 from 83.
fuller, on the middle and leg, flicked to Lee at fine leg
shout for a catch down the leg side as Bravo misses the glance and it brushes the hip en route to Ronchi.
short in length, pushed to the on side
leans across to square drive on the up to deep cover
short of length, outside off stump, Chanderpaul cuts it down to third man for a single.
slashed through the vacant slip region. Short in length and cutting away from Chanderpaul who went back and across and went hard with his cut shot. It flew off the outer half of the blade
oh he tries to sweep, yes sweep, Watson from well outside and misses. Chanderpaul is looking to go after Watto here
outside the off stump, mistimes the cut and will rush across for a quick single
slips down leg, Bravo flicks it very fine. 211 for 3.
leans forward to push a length delivery to covers
wide down the leg side. 71 from 73 and Watson runs to the top of his run up.
turns a length delivery from outside off to long-on for a single. The batsmen get across to have a chat
leans forward to drive a full delivery to Symonds at extra cover.
banged in short on the leg side. Bravo mistimes the pull to leg slip region. It went off his gloves
wide down the leg side. Ronchi does well to collect that. Johnson is furious with himself.
short in length and coming into Chanderpaul who rocks back to pull to deep midwicket. He then suggests he should have got it squarer.
on the middle and leg, nudged to midwicket

stands tall to punch a back-of-length delivery to Symonds. They think about a run, Symonds tries to kill the thought with a direct hit at the striker's end but it ricochets off the stumps for the overthrows.
Bravo goes down town. Full pitched and driven beautifully down the ground. All along the carpet
Fabulous extra-cover drive. Sensational hit. It was a length delivery around the off stump and he leaned into the shot and lifted it inside-out over the off side field.
leans forward to defend
short of length delivery on the off stump line, pushed back to the bowler
leans forward to push to the on side and runs with the stroke
pushed to the on side and is cut off the straightish midwicket fielder.
short in length and angling away from Bravo who has a huge flash at it. The crowd sigh in relief that he didn't get a nick
stands tall to punch a length delivery to long-off
slings in a full delivery, tailing in to the middle, worked to midwicket
Pressure. Wide outside leg stump and Ronchi dives but can't prevent it from running to the boundary. Clarke holds his head. Agony. Crowd show their joy.
short in length, outside off stump, cut past point.
fuller, on the middle and leg, pushed to long-on
Chanderpaul retains the strike with a drive to long-on
outside the off stump, cut down to third man

Bravo opens the bat-face and runs a length delivery to third man. Bravo waits to see whether it has crossed the backward point fielder before he runs. Once they complete the single, Chanderpaul has a chat with Bravo.
full and just outside off, squeezed down to third man
length delivery on the middle and leg, tapped to left of short fine leg
slower one outside off stump, gets a under edge on the waft and will pick up a single to right of third man
angling across Chanderpaul who opens the blade and runs it to third man
short in length, moving towards legs , Bravo tries to pull it, misses and it strikes the pad
fuller and outside off, lifted inside-out to left of long-off where Johnson makes a sliding stop
short  and on the middle and leg, drags his pull to long leg
driven to long-off for a single. 36 from 43

Clatter. The off cutter, full in length, shaping in towards the middle and off, Bravo plays all around it. Yet another twist. Australia continue to hustle. West Indies fight on. 36 from 42 and this dead-rubber is alive and kicking.
full and angling down leg, brushes the pad and goes to Ronchi
on the middle and leg, off a length, clipped to deep midwicket

fires in a 88.7 mph yorker swinging in on the middle and leg line, some how he manages to get his bat down and stabs it down the track. = What a delivery to receive first up in your international career.
follows up the yorker with a bouncer. Findlay takes his eyes off and ducks. The ball crashes into his back and rolls to short fine leg region.
leans forward to push to the off side
short in length, mistimes his pull to wide mid-on region
full and outside off stump, driven to left of sweeper cover

leans across, goes down on his knee to slog-sweep a short of length delivery to deep backward square leg region where David Hussey makes a fine stop near the  ropes. He throws the ball into play and dives over the ropes.
slanted across, cutting away, pushed to extra cover.
short in length, cutting away from Findlay who tries to punch hard but mistimes the shot to mid-off.
fuller, the slow off cutter, trying to trap him lbw but Findlay gets his bat around the pad and turns to square leg. Three dot balls.
One more as he mistimes a pull to midwicket. He shakes his head as he walks across to have a chat with Chanderpaul
short in length, coming in to Chanderpaul who short-arm pulls to deep backward square leg.
yorker length delivery on the off and middle, Findlay was ready this time and digs it out towards mid-off and rushes across for the single. Chanderpaul back on strike. 26 from 28. Lee rushes in.
Ah ... the slower one, Chanderpaul checks his shot and laps it around the corner to fine leg for a single
Another yorker, squeezed to square leg
the yorker ends up as a low dipping full toss, pushed back to Lee who turns around quickly to confirm the bad news. Free hit coming up.
clears the front leg, Lee fires it short and outside off, flat-batted to deep cover
Bouncer. Findlay ducks in time. End of the Lee over.
full and well outside the off stump, Chanderpaul presses across to slice it to covers
on a length, pushed across FIndlay who dabs to backward point. He was looking for a single but there is none.

Omg! Findlay goes down town. After dabbing around, trying to get the single to get Chanderpaul on strike and failing, he decides to go for the jugular. He thrust his front foot and lifted a full delivery over long-on. Hopes kicks the ground in disgust.
mistimes a pull past midwicket
leans forward to drive to long-off. One to go this over. What will Findlay do?
off cutter, moves past the forward prod, strikes Ronchi's pad and hits the sticks.
the slower one outside off, from round the stumps, dabbed to right of third man. The throw comes in and FIndlay tries to steal a extra run for the over throw but Chanderpaul sends him back

What a stunner from Michael Hussey at midwicket. The game swings around once more. Findlay tries to force a full length delivery and it flies off the inner half well to the left of Hussey who dives full stretch with his left arm outstretched and some how manages to pluck the ball. Awesome.

How did that yorker miss the off stump. Lee can't believe it. He looks past the batsman, waiting for the bails to fall. No luck. Ramdin was late in getting the bat down, the yorker just escapes the bottom edge and rushes past the off stump.
Another searing yorker, stabbed to midwicket. Superb bowling at the death.
full and fast, squeezed to the off side.
Full and outside off, swing and a miss. Lee's ten overs are over.

walks across the stumps, Bracken bowls the slow yorker, Chanderpaul can't connect with the waft across the line and is struck on the pad just outside off. They shout for the lbw. Bucknor shakes his head and signals leg bye
the captain Clarke misfields a delivery hit straight to him at backward point . Hmm...
turns a slower one to fine leg. 9 from 9.
on a length, around off, cut down to left of backward point. Clarke fields this time and has a shy at the non-striker's end. Misses but the batsman was home anyway.
another one released with the scrambled seam, worked to midwicket. No run.

The death rattle. Chanderpaul goes down on his knee and tries to swing the slow off cutter, misses and the off stump is pegged back. Bracken roars. The crowd sigh. Darren Sammy walks out to join Ramdin. Game is on the knife edge.
homing in on the off stump, cut to cover point for a single.
short in length and outside off stump ,cut to deep point for a single. Gayle is sitting on the staircase to the dressing room and looks at the action.
fuller, on the middle, clears the front foot and drives to long-on. Clarke has a chat with Watto. More advice from the crowd.
The slower one, full in length and pushed to mid-on region. The crowd check the scoreboard. Four from two.

Ramdin can only get a single from a mistimed pull to square leg where Hopes makes a tumbling stop. Aussies hustle till the very end. Three from 1. Sammy looks up to the skies. Watson waits at the top of the run up

Australia have won! just a single to covers. Low dipping full toss on the middle, hit straight to Clarke. Gayle is dejected and stares in to the distance. The Aussies are in a huddle. They break away and walk towards the pavilion. Gayle now stirs and walks down the staircase to shake hands with them, Fidel is downcast. He is hunched down on the staircase and he now slowly stands and follows his captain. Bravo is out there with Gayle. Game over.
